history.content:
Haven't taken some of those classes yet but I don't think EE16A or CS188 is a good idea. EE 126 is supposed to be more work than CS 70, and 61C definitely feels like more work than 61B. Not sure how 188/16A would compare to 110 but it already seems like its a heavier workload than what you're taking now.

----------

If you want to have free time, do not take 61C, 126, and 16A at the same time. 16A will probably not be hard for you but it does take some time. 61C, 126, and 188 would be slightly better (188 is low time commitment and the probability it requires will be easier since you'll have 126) but still not relaxing by any means. 16A, 61C, and 188 would be doable.

----------

Haven't taken some of those classes yet but I don't think EE16A or CS188 is a good idea. EE 126 is supposed to be more work than CS 70, and 61C definitely feels like more work than 61B. Not sure how 188/16A would compare to 110 but it already seems like its a heavier workload than what you're taking now.

----------

I'm a first year who is interested in learning more about statistics and probability, so I am thinking of taking EE 126 in the fall. Firstly, I am wondering if 126, 61C and either 16A or 188 will be too much work. If so, I'll be taking 16A, 61C, and 188 instead. For choosing between 16A and 188: I haven't started the 16 series yet but since I am currently in 110 my friends tell me 16A shouldn't be very difficult. My older friends advise me to take 188 because it doesn't have a high workload but will help me figure out what I'm interested in. Not sure what to do ):

I've taken 61A, 61B, 70, 53, and 110 so far in terms of relevant technicals. Currently, I'm taking 70, 61B, 110 and I have a significant time commitment to my fellowship (10 hours a week) and I'm also involved in a different club (~5 hours a week). 110 has been more of a struggle because I had almost no prior exposure to linear algebra before, but I've been doing okay after I caught up in the beginning of the semester. I'll probably make A-'s if I'm lucky, B-'s if I'm not but I'm really sick of having no free time this semester so I'd like it if my next semester wasn't so work work work in general. 

ALSO, what should I phase 1? I KNOW THIS WAS SO LONG I am so sorry but thank you so much!
